{
    "analysis": "You computed global P95/P05 per (cmdb_id,kpi) and counted anomalies inside the incident window. Results show many services report anomalies starting around 2024-01-21T06:31:00Z. A large cluster of socket and diskio KPIs across many services/databases (carts, catalogue and catalogue-db, session-db, rabbitmq and rabbitmq-exporter, queue-master, user and user-db, orders-db, payment, front-end) all show anomalies. Some metrics show balanced high/low counts of 25/25 which likely stems from thresholds equal to observed constant values (e.g., P95==P05 or P95==0) causing both high- and low- conditions to be counted — this requires caution when interpreting those as true faults. The earliest anomaly timestamps cluster at ~06:31:00Z, suggesting a system-wide event then. Traces and error_logs are empty, so we must use metric and log.csv only. Next, we should use log telemetry to check for elevated application error counts or sudden drops in row_count (traffic) during the window to distinguish whether the problem is application errors, network (socket) issues, or I/O issues.",
